<br>
Anyways ... when you port up you will find yourself in a little enclosure.  I would suggest printing one of the maps on www.eqmaps.com as it will help orient you and help you know where to go.  If there is no 55+ Mage there doing CoH you will have to run to the safe wall.  Don't worry about the run much ... hopefully someone in your port group has been there before and you can just follow them.  You will be running along the middle of a slanted wall.  Don't let your head hit the roof but don't get too low ... stay in the middle as you run.  If you get aggroed stop and die ... the raid will be very pissed at you if you train the safe wall.  Your body will be dragged and rezzed.<br>
<br>
Once everyone is there pulls will start.  Nuke when you have mana ... likely you will not be allowed to use a pet and for your first trip I would suggest you don't even if they did allow it.  Pathing up there is fux0red.  Mod rods aren't needed too much except to help Cleric mana on rezzing after a wipe out.  Oh ... expect a wipe out or two unless you're with a very experienced group.  Wipe outs are just a part of Hate and usually happen early on in the raid.<br>
<br>
One thing that sucks about Mage loot is that it drops of Male Revenants, which are in the far NE corner of the zone.  The safe wall and Maestro's hall (raids move here usually after the west houses are cleared) are on the west and northwest side of the zone respectively.  That means the Revenants are normally pulled last.  If there are alot of problems like wipe outs, puller LD or others then the raid may end before all the Revenants are pulled.  This really sucks but it's the way it goes.  I usually see 2-3 pieces of Apothic drop per clearing on average.<br>
<br>
Don't nuke until the MOB is at about 70% to avoid aggro and just listen to the raid leader and you'll be fine.  Oh and don't nuke the Spite Golems ... they're 100% MR and will be a waste of your mana.  Good luck ... you'll have a blast.  I've been up there many times and I still have lots of fun when I go.<br>
<br>
 <p><fontcolor=FF0000><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=24305">Kalamos</a></b></font><br>57th High Elf Conjurer</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usehra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sehra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 196<br> <font color=#333333>(11/7/01 3:07:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: First time in Hate</span><hr size=1> Actually, apothic gloves and sleeves are also pretty darn nice. I prefer them to kelp, but I must admit that Thurg quest armor is better, and SS/Kael blow them out of the water.<br>
<br>
But who cares? It's HATE! It's fun, provided your puller isn't an idiot. Or your tagger. Or your chanter(s), or your clerics, or your...well, so long as everyone keeps their head on, it'l be fun. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Things to make sure you have/know before the raid:<br>
<br>
1) Have a hotkey for targetted assist (/ass)<br>
<br>
2) Know who the main assist is, and have a HK for them. (/ass CurlyFriesTheGnome)<br>
<br>
3) Don't even have gate memmed. I stick modrod there for all &quot;stand and die&quot; raids. You don't gate, EVER, unless you are told to. And you most likely won't be until the raid is over. <br>
<br>
3a) If things go to hell, your job is to provide cover fire for the clerics to camp. If (after you're comfortable with the zone) you are allowed pets, you can do alot to help them.<br>
<br>
4) Print out a map of the zone, it's great to know where you are. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
5) If you are allowed pets (see above - hate has evil evil pathing), have your earthenboots in a main box and have that box hotkeyed. <br>
<br>
<br>
Sorry if I was a bit grumpy or longwinded. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  But good luck, and have fun! Hate can be a blast with the right group.<br>
